title: Jordan 4 Yellow Thunder
body: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Thunder’ brings back the coveted colorway originally released in 2006 (and previously reissued in 2012). The upper is draped in smooth black nubuck, contrasted by hits of yellow on the molded eyelets, quarter panel, and lower tongue, with the latter two components covered in black netting. Jumpman branding appears on the Flight tongue tag and molded heel tab. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel.

title: Nike Airmax 1 Patta Aqua Noise (With Bracelet)
Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite
Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott Black Phantom
New Balance 550 White Green
body: The New Balance 550 ‘White Green’ showcases a throwback hardwood design lifted directly from the brand’s late ‘80s archives. White leather is utilized on the upper, featuring microperforated paneling and a tonal suede overlay that wraps around the toe. Forest green accents make their way to the sneaker’s various branding elements, including a raised ‘N’ logo and an oversized tongue tag marked with ‘New Balance 550.’ The low-profile silhouette sits on a rubber cupsole with soft EVA cushioning.

title: Adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Carbon
body: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Carbon’ features a breathable Primeknit upper in a neutral black and grey finish. The sneaker’s lateral side features a streak of black via the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, separating a light grey weave up top with mostly black construction on the lower half. No-tie bungee laces deliver a secure fit. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a yellow-tinged rubber cage.

title: Adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Dazzling Blue
body: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Dazzling Blue’ delivers a two-tone colorway of Kanye West’s popular lifestyle runner. The minimalist upper features flexible Primeknit construction, pitched to a solid black hue with contrasting threads woven throughout. A streak of royal blue cuts through the lateral side, complete with signature SPLY-350 branding. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, entirely wrapped in a semi-translucent TPU cage for added durability.

title: Nike Dunk Low Two Tone Pure Platinum
body: Versatile in appearance, this Nike Dunk Low comes dressed in a leather upper with Light Grey taking care of the underlays and a darker shade of Grey taking care of the overlays, lining, insoles, and rubber outsole. Light contrast comes by way of the White used on the Swoosh branding, laces and midsole. Light Blue nylon tongues complete the look.

title: Nike Dunk Low Lottery Green
body: This Dunk Low SE has a “Pale Ivory/ Black/ Malachite” colour scheme. The smooth leather base of the shoe is Pale Ivory. The striking smooth leather overlays are in none other than the titular lush Malachite. The signature profile Swooshes on both the medial and lateral sides of the shoes are in standout black. Nike’s diamond-adorned lottery-inspired branding appears on the Malachite tongue tab and the white insole. A scratch-off coin hangtag comes with the shoe. A Sail-coloured midsole and a Malachite rubber outsole round out the sneaker’s look

title: Jordan 4 Infrared
body: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Infrared’ features distinctive color blocking that recalls the ‘Green Glow’ AJ4 release from 2013. The upper is crafted from smooth nubuck in a charcoal finish. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while black accents land on the quarter panel netting, structural wings and Jumpman-branded heel tab. The sneaker’s titular hue lights up the woven tongue tag and a quartet of molded eyelets. A polyurethane midsole packs visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel for a smooth ride.

title: Jordan 1 Mid Ice Blue GS
body: The Air Jordan 1 Mid GS 'Ice Blue' has an all-smooth-leather upper. The base is two-toned, with black covering the toe box, white on the mid-panels and black again on the collar underlay. This black-and-white look is joined by the titular Ice Blue colour on the toe cap, the mudguard, the eye stay panel and the heel counter. The signature profile Swooshes on both the medial and the lateral sides of the shoe are black, matching the toe box and collar. Angelic white Wings logos are embossed on the lateral collar flaps. A pure white midsole and an Ice Blue rubber outsole wrap up the look of this shoe.
